Hi! On my Windows 7 installation, I have device with non ascii description, due this I get UnicodeEncodeError here: infi.devicemanager/src/infi/devicemanager/__init__.py on line 21.

return "<{}>".format(self.friendly_name if self.has_property("friendly_name")else self.description)

replacing "<{}>" with u"<{}>" fix it, but i did not dig deeply into this, is it safe to fix it this way?

I noticed that the minified bootstrap.min.css from getbootstrap.com includes a rule: 

```css
*{
  -moz-box-sizing:border-box;
}
```

to help with old Firefox shenanigans. (in this case, I was using Firefox 10 ::shudders::)


When I included

```scss
@import "bootstrap-sprockets";
@import "bootstrap";
```
in my app, that declaration was missing.


adding it back in manually made columns work as I expected.


Thanks for bootstrap-sass! It is fantastic and I love using it.

